{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-markdown-js","path":"/blueprints/blueprint/docs/adr/0014-enforcing-resource-quotas.md","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Operate First"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c97873ce-84e9-505d-b848-0c020d960d6d","html":"<h1 id=\"enforcing-of-resource-quotas\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#enforcing-of-resource-quotas\" aria-label=\"enforcing of resource quotas permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Enforcing of Resource Quotas</h1>\n<p>Technical Story: <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/apps/issues/438\">1</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/apps/pull/439\">2</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"context-and-problem-statement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#context-and-problem-statement\" aria-label=\"context and problem statement permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Context and Problem Statement</h2>\n<p>Currently clusters being managed by Operate-First are not enforcing quotas on compute and storage resources. This means that anyone can use their <code class=\"language-text\">namespace</code> to use hog as many resources as they wish. We should use Kubernetes’ <a href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/policy/resource-quotas/\">ResourceQuotas</a> to address this concern. Decisions for declaring quotas for resource <code class=\"language-text\">requests</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">limits</code> should be guided by monitoring current trends and usage via available dashboards. We will also need to add default <a href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/manage-resources/memory-default-namespace/\">LimitRanges</a> so current workloads are not prevented from creating resources.</p>\n<h2 id=\"considered-options\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#considered-options\" aria-label=\"considered options permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Considered Options</h2>\n<p>The only option is to use <a href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/policy/resource-quotas/\">ResourceQuotas</a>, what is subject to debate is how we organize/advertise these quotas in git.</p>\n<h3 id=\"1-tiered--custom-resource-quotas\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-tiered--custom-resource-quotas\" aria-label=\"1 tiered  custom resource quotas permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Tiered &#x26; Custom Resource quotas</h3>\n<p>We identify a tier of standard <code class=\"language-text\">ResourceQuotas</code> that we distribute to each namespace. We will adhere to this tiered system as much as possible, but acknowledge the need for custom quotas, and allow for such exceptions on a need basis. <code class=\"language-text\">ResourceQuotas</code> can be included as <code class=\"language-text\">Kustomize</code> components</p>\n<h3 id=\"pros\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pros\" aria-label=\"pros permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pros:</h3>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>User friendly. It’s a lot easier to tell a new-comer to pick from a set of options then to specify specific requirements.</li>\n<li>Consistency. Tiers ensure that all new-comers are treated the same and any custom request is treated more carefully.</li>\n<li>Easy to propagate changes. For example, should we decide to update all <code class=\"language-text\">small</code> tier <code class=\"language-text\">ResourceQuotas</code>, we need only update one manifest in git.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"cons\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cons\" aria-label=\"cons permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cons:</h3>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>May result in waste of compute resources since we’re trying to fit various use cases into a small set of tiered options.</li>\n<li>Could get convoluted if custom <code class=\"language-text\">ResourceQuotas</code> manifests start drastically outnumbering the standard options.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"2-only-resource-quotas\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-only-resource-quotas\" aria-label=\"2 only resource quotas permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Only Resource quotas</h3>\n<p>No tier option, every namespace has a resource quota customized for their needs.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pros-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pros-1\" aria-label=\"pros 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pros:</h3>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>Less likely to waste resources if tuned correctly for each namespace.</li>\n<li>There’s no confusion over when to use a tiered option or custom (since there’s only custom option)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"cons-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cons-1\" aria-label=\"cons 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cons:</h3>\n<ul class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>Adds additional overhead to the on-boarding process, as now we require new-comers to assess their exact resource needs to fully benefit from this option.</li>\n<li>More resources to track and manage.</li>\n<li>Each admin can have their own view of what exact quota is necessary for a given project and this can lead to uncertainty and different quota based on who is serving the onboarding ticket.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"preferred-option\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#preferred-option\" aria-label=\"preferred option permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Preferred option</h2>\n<p>Option 1 is preferred, due to the flexibility it offers. If it comes to the point where everyone is opting for <code class=\"language-text\">custom</code> quotas anyway, we can simply abandon the tier option.</p>\n<h2 id=\"outcomes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#outcomes\" aria-label=\"outcomes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Outcomes</h2>","fields":{"srcLink":"https://github.com/operate-first/blueprint/blob/master/docs/adr/0014-enforcing-resource-quotas.md"},"frontmatter":{"title":"","description":null,"extraClasses":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"c97873ce-84e9-505d-b848-0c020d960d6d"}},"staticQueryHashes":["117426894","3000541721","3606484676","533861647"]}